                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities, 1931/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Consul at Bluefields</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rowe</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 18, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 17, 6 p.m., third paragraph. The Naval vessels now on duty at Puerto
                    Cabezas, Bluefields, and Cape Gracias a Dios will remain until the present
                    difficulty is over.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
